<Author>madera99
<Content>Nice Hotel - A few Complaints I stayed here for 3 nights in September for business. The hotel feels safe and is in a decent location. It is close to shopping and restaurants but a taxi is necessary.The room was big and modern. I think the bed was a little hard, but there is a large flat screen tv and the bathroom was very nice. The restaurant downstairs is decent. The menu is not big and the service is a little slow, but the food is fine.My biggest complaint about this hotel is the wireless internet service. It is horrible! All three days at the hotel- the service was spotty at best. I called the front desk and I believe they know they have problems with the wireless internet. (internet with an ethernet cable is not available). The front desk was very rude about the problem as it seemed as though they are also frustrated by it. 
