<Author>Dreloso
<Content>Good experience, but... Stayed a week at the Royal while visiting my daughter who is a college student in Mexico City. Overall a very good experience. Price was same as I booked via Travelocity and the room was very nice and clean. Service was very good and the lobby restaurant was exceptional for a lobby restaurant. Nice pool and spa. Now for the however....lots of street noise at night even though the room is quite some distance off the street. The location is in a business complex area with no shops or restaurants within walking distance, so a taxi ride is necessary for everything. Finally, I arranged through the front desk for a taxi the airport at the end of our stay at a fixed rate. The driver did the classic and raised the price once we got to the airport.Overall a nice hotel and good experience. 
